        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Since the wooden framework is to be carried by the Merarites, these three expressions denote only the stuff hangings; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 4:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". An explanation of the terms is found in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 26:1-14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". As an ordinary tent consists mainly of the covering, the wood-work being only an accessory to support it, so (1) the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "tabernacle",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (or rather dwelling) proper consisted of ten strips of linen worked in three colours with figures of cherubim, and joined by hooks and loops into one whole (",
        "children": []
